<title>UK: Russian soldier kills six after fleeing unit.</title>
<headline>Russian soldier kills six after fleeing unit.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>A Russian soldier in the Far East killed six people in an exchange of gunfire after fleeing his unit, Radio Russia reported on Friday.</p>
<p>The radio, monitored by the British Broadcasting Corporation, said the soldier fled from his unit in the Transbaykal Military District on Thursday night after shooting a guard with an assault rifle.</p>
<p>&quot;Six people died in the exchange of fire,&quot; the radio said, adding that troops were searching for the soldier.</p>
